Name: 565 Elderflower Lane, New York, NY 11443
Summary: This converted 1970's townhouse provides a welcome respite from the bustling streets of New York. A downtown location with an uptown feel, modern fixtures in a stately layout, it's a home that provides a taste of country luxury in the heart of the city. The 3 bedrooms are all queen-sized with adjoining bathrooms, with the exception of the master bedroom, which features an en-suite spa-style bathroom. Tucked away in a quiet street in the West Village, and located next to diverse restaurants and bars, as well as a farmer's market, this address offers it all.

Name: 25 Four Eyck Place, Brooklyn, NY 18731
Summary: Truly modern, this townhouse comes complete with furnishings designed by the Ralph Lauren team. With high-quality oak accents throughout the home, this modern New York address provides a bit of nature in the busy city. The expansive kitchen opens into a modern green space, featuring a deck and garden.

Name: 822 Fennel Road, New York, NY 13421
Summary: A home that has the versatility to be the ultimate bachelor(ette) home, or the cozy abode of a modern, high-powered family. High-quality fixtures with built-in smart home tech makes for seamless, easy living.

Name: One Queen's Lane, Brooklyn, NY 12429
Summary: Every room in this expansive loft feature exposed brick, offering a rustic vibe in a modern neighborhood. Space is maximized in this luxury apartment, with a king sized bedroom, and living space that suggests this could have been a multiple bedroom home. Nearby restaurants include the famed Taco's, well known local businesses such as Street Lights Books, and New York Ice Cream.

Name: 16 Chartreuse Street, Brooklyn, NY 17429
Summary: This 2 bedroom home is a modern escape in the heart of Brooklyn's Seaside Heights. Designed to provide an island home ambience, you can take advantage of a fully modern kitchen, sunlit living room or contemporary dining room in this beachfront property located near the cultural districts of Brighton Beach and Coney Island.

Name: 754 Ashford Street, Westhampton, NY 14724
Summary: Even the most sophisticated jaws will drop when you walk into this beautiful beachside home. With accents drawing directly from the ocean (conveniently located 50 feet away),  highly-modern fixtures, and smart-home features allow you to live peacefully, effortlessly.
